You are a security researcher at a fraud immunity lab generating synthetic account takeover (ATO) fraud scenarios. These scenarios are used exclusively to train and evaluate behavioral anomaly detection systems — never for actual attacks.

Generate a single, detailed ATO fraud scenario as a JSON object. The scenario must model the full attack lifecycle: compromise, reconnaissance, and monetization.

## Attack Parameters
- Attack type: account_takeover
- Complexity: {{ complexity }}
- Target segment: {{ target_segment }}
- Required evasion tactics: {{ evasion_tactics | join(", ") }}

## Output Schema (strict — return ONLY this JSON, no explanation)
{
  "attack_type": "account_takeover",
  "complexity": "{{ complexity }}",
  "target_segment": "{{ target_segment }}",
  "evasion_tactics": ["<tactic_1>", "<tactic_2>", ...],
  "transaction_pattern": {
    "compromise_vector": "<credential_stuffing|sim_swap|malware|session_hijack|insider>",
    "reconnaissance_phase": {
      "duration_minutes": <integer 0-60>,
      "actions": ["<view_balance|check_payees|review_limits|change_contact_info>", ...]
    },
    "device_changes": {
      "fingerprint_changed": <true|false>,
      "new_device_enrolled": <true|false>,
      "device_type": "<mobile|desktop|emulated>"
    },
    "contact_info_changes": {
      "email_changed": <true|false>,
      "phone_changed": <true|false>,
      "mfa_method_changed": <true|false>
    },
    "new_payee_additions": <integer 0-5>,
    "time_to_first_transfer_minutes": <integer 5-120>,
    "monetization": [
      {
        "step": 1,
        "type": "<internal_transfer|external_wire|p2p|bill_pay|crypto>",
        "amount_ratio": <0.0-1.0, fraction of available balance>,
        "delay_minutes": <integer>,
        "new_payee": <true|false>
      }
    ]
  },
  "expected_detection_signals": [
    "<device_fingerprint_change|new_payee_high_value|behavioral_drift_transaction|contact_info_change_before_transfer|velocity_spike|...>"
  ]
}

## Constraints
- monetization list must have 1-4 entries.
- reconnaissance_phase.actions must have at least 1 entry.
- Do NOT include real usernames, passwords, email addresses, or phone numbers.
- Use only synthetic placeholder values.
- expected_detection_signals must name at least 3 specific, distinct signals.
- Return only the JSON object — no markdown, no explanation.
